Hi,

I think thats a bad practice. Better use:

try {
  // exception t=
hrowing statement.
  fail(&quot;NullPointerException expected!&quot;);
} catch (NullP=
ointerException e) {
  // optional asserts on the exception message or exce=
ption cause.
}

Other exceptions are thrown through, so the
test fails for =
all other nonexpected exceptions.

For JUnit4 instead use:

@Test(expected=
=3DNullPointerException.class)
public void testIsThrowingNullPointerExcepti=
on() {
  // exception throwing statement.
}
